\begin_layout Subsubsection
Spectral Irradiance
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The spectral irradiance measures the power density of solar radiation at specific wavelengths at the top of atmosphere (TOA) and may be found in tables of measured values.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The following diagram shows the spectral irradiance over the visible spectrum from the ASTMG173 data set.
